What is Helm?

Helm is the package manager for Kubernetes. Just as "apt install nginx"  installs and configures NGINX on Ubuntu, Helm can install complex Kubernetes applications with a single command.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is a Helm Chart?

A Helm Chart is a package containing everything needed to deploy an application.

        "helm install my-nginx bitnami/nginx"

Here:

Chart = bitnami/nginx (the package)
Release = my-nginx (the installed instance)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

what is release : it is the running instance of the chart running in k8s cluster 

Easiest Way to Remember
Think of it like this:

Chart = Blueprint 📄
Release = Building built from that blueprint 🏢

      "helm install my-nginx bitnami/nginx"

Here:

Chart = bitnami/nginx (the package)
Release = my-nginx (the installed instance)


We can use same chart for deploying in multiple/same environemnt by using different release name 

      
      "helm install Dev bitnami/nginx"
      
      "helm install Prod bitnami/nginx"

Here:

Chart = bitnami/nginx  (the package)
Release = Dev & Prod   (the installed instance)
-----------------------------

Why is it called a Release?

When Helm installs a chart, it "releases" that application into the Kubernetes cluster.

That deployed application is called a Release.

Each release contains:

  The deployed Kubernetes resources (Deployment, Service, ConfigMap, etc.)
  The configuration used (values.yaml)
  The chart version
  The release history (used for upgrades and rollbacks)


